
Overview of noun hegira

The noun hegira has 2 senses (no senses from tagged texts)
                                       
1. Hegira, Hejira -- (the flight of Muhammad from Mecca to Medina in 622 which marked the beginning of the Muslim era; the Muslim calendar begins in that year)
2. exodus, hegira, hejira -- (a journey by a large group to escape from a hostile environment)
